JOHANNESBURG - Coach Stuart Baxter will on Thursday announce his Bafana Bafana squad to face Senegal in back-to-back World Cup qualifiers.  South Africa take on the Lions of Teranga on Friday, 10 November at Peter Mokaba Stadium in Polokwane. The two nations will again lock horns four days later (Tuesday, 14 November) in the final clash of the qualifiers at Stade Leopold Sedar Senghor in Dakar, Senegal. Bafana are fourth on the Group D table with four points, while Senegal top the group with eight points with two matches remaining.
	
	Burkina Faso and Cape Verde are on six points each.  African News Agency